legacy.full_text: Breaking News: If the U.S. had begun imposing social distancing measures one week earlier than it did in March, about 36,000 fewer people would have died in the coronavirus outbreak, according to new estimates from Columbia University researchers https://t.co/phnyEgZice

If the US had begun locking down cities & limiting social contact on March 1, 2 weeks earlier than most people started staying home, the vast majority of the nation’s deaths — about 83 percent — would have been avoided, researchers say. What a difference!
